 from both\nabsorption and emission lines. The spectral energy distribution (SED) of the\nafterglow has a power-law shape with slope beta=0.56+-0.04. This can be\ncompared to the X-ray spectral index which is betaX=1.0+-0.1. The curvature of\nthe SED constrain the dust reddening towards the burst to Av<0.5 mag.\n(abridged)\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 25 Jan 2007 18:36:53 GMT"}],"update_date":"2008-11-26"}
