gly suggest a dense and/or large circumstellar disk. HD 110432\nhas several properties reminiscence of the cataclysmic variables such as a very\nhot X-ray temperature and its detailed spectral features. This suggests that it\nmight be a Be star harbouring an accreting white dwarf. On the other hand,\naccumulating evidence of magnetic activities in the literature supports the\nsurface-disk of the star as being the X-ray site.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 26 Jan 2007 12:43:12 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Wed, 14 Feb 2007 00:38:39 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Mon, 27 Aug 2007 17:54:01 GMT"},{"version":"v4","created":"Thu, 30 Aug 2007 16:58:15 GMT"}],"update_date":"2009-11-13"}
